 x1c4vz4f x2lah0s x1pg5gke xdzw4kq x193iq5w x1xxsxie x7r5mf7 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 xlyipyv xuxw1ft" data-testid="cell-frame-primary-detail"><span class="x140p0ai x1gufx9m x1s928wv xhkezso x1gmr53x x1cpjm7i x1fgarty x1943h6x x193iq5w xeuugli x13faqbe x1vvkbs x1lliihq x1fj9vlw xhslqc4 x1hx0egp x1pg5gke xjb2p0i xo1l8bm xl2ypbo x1ic7a3i" style="--x-fontSize: 12px; --x-lineHeight: 8.5313px; --x-8dd7yt: -0.0137em; --x-hxtmnb: 0.0137em;">Yesterday</span></div></div><div class="x6s0dn4 xhslqc4 x78zum5 x1nxh6w3 x1fc57z9 xr9ek0c xisnujt" data-testid="cell-frame-secondary"><div class="xjbqb8w x1iyjqo2 x1f6kntn x1fc57z9 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1yc453h xlyipyv xuxw1ft xo1l8bm"><span class="x78zum5 x1cy8zhl" title="‪Short answer: it depends what you&#39;re doing

- Starting fresh → git clone &lt;url&gt;  
  This connects to the repo AND downloads everything. That&#39;s the &quot;connect + download&quot; command.

- You already have the files locally → git remote add origin &lt;url&gt;  
  This just tells your local folder &quot;hey, this repo over here is the remote to sync with&quot;. You&#39;d use this if you did git init first, or downloaded a zip.

The usual flow 
New project from GitHub/GitLab:
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
Existing local folder you want to push:
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
To check what remotes you have: git remote -v

Which situation are you in? Cloning something down, or connecting a folder you already made?‬" data-testid="last-msg-status"><span dir="auto" class="x1iyjqo2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1n2onr6 xlyipyv xuxw1ft x1rg5ohu xnpuxes" style="min-height: 0px;">Short answer: it depends what you're doing

- Starting fresh → git clone &lt;url&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;This connects to the repo AND downloads everything. That's the "connect + download" command.

- You already have the files locally → git remote add origin &lt;url&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;This just tells your local folder "hey, this repo over here is the remote to sync with". You'd use this if you did git init first, or downloaded a zip.

The usual flow&nbsp;
New project from GitHub/GitLab:
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
Existing local folder you want to push:
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
To check what remotes you have: git remote -v

Which situation are you in? Cloning something down, or connecting a folder you already made?</span></span></div><div role="gridcell" aria-colindex="1" class="xhslqc4 x1c4vz4f x2lah0s x1pg5gke x1fc57z9 xdzw4kq x193iq5w"><span class=""></span><span class=""></span><span class="xtrg13t"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="x10l6tqk xh8yej3 x1g42fcv" role="row" data-testid="list-item-2" style="z-index: 60; transition: none; height: 76px; transform: translateY(152px);"><div role="gridcell" class="x1n2onr6" tabindex="0"><div tabindex="-1" class="" aria-selected="false"><div data-testid="cell-frame-container" class="x1280gxy xlr9sxt xvvg52n xwd4zgb xq8v1ta x78zum5 x1q0g3np xy75621 x1hm9lzh x1sa5p1d x71s49j x1n2onr6 x1ypdohk x1ubxc9n xbmkbis x1yjtglu xiitwr3 x206yn3"><div class="x78zum5"><div class="x6s0dn4 x78zum5 x1c4vz4f x2lah0s x1y332i5 x18d9i69 xexx8yu x1n1b19v xbmws1g"><div><div class="x1n2onr6 x1c9tyrk xeusxvb x1pahc9y x1ertn4p" style="height: 49px; width: 49px;"><img alt="" draggable="false" class="x1n2onr6 x1lliihq xh8yej3 x5yr21d x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1c9tyrk xeusxvb x1pahc9y x1ertn4p xl1xv1r x115dhu7 x17vty23 x1hc1fzr x4u6w88 x1g40iwv xnpuxes" tabindex="-1" src="./WhatsApp_files/file(1).enc" style="visibility: visible;"></div></div></div></div><div class="x78zum5 xdl72j9 xdt5ytf x1iyjqo2 xl56j7k xeuugli x1n1b19v"><div role="gridcell" aria-colindex="2" class="x6s0dn4 x78zum5 xggjnk3 x1yc453h"><div class="x14ug900 x78zum5 x1iyjqo2 x1jchvi3 xdod15v x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1mzt3pk x1yc453h xo1l8bm" data-testid="cell-frame-title"><div class="x1c4vz4f xuce83p x1bft6iq x1i7k8ik xq9mrsl x6s0dn4 x78zum5"><div class="xuxw1ft x6ikm8r x10wlt62 xlyipyv x78zum5"><span dir="auto" title="Holyfield" class="x1iyjqo2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1n2onr6 xlyipyv xuxw1ft x1rg5ohu x1jchvi3 xjb2p0i xo1l8bm x17mssa0 x1ic7a3i xnpuxes" style="min-height: 0px;">Holyfield</span></div></div></div><div class="xhslqc4 x1c4vz4f x2lah0s x1pg5gke xdzw4kq x193iq5w x1xxsxie x7r5mf7 x6ikm8r x10wl