</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq"><blockquote dir="ltr" class="x1rg5ohu x1n2onr6 xh8yej3 xhslqc4 xav9cv8 x4tpdpg xnpuxes selectable-text copyable-text" data-testid="selectable-text" data-pre-plain-text="&gt; "><div class="x10l6tqk x1o0tod x13vifvy x5yr21d x1g8rjiy x1518k6t xkqq1k2 x91jh78 x1xkn691 x4oqio7"></div><div class="x1rg5ohu x1gx403c xj0a0fe xeaf4i8">You are a senior Next.js performance engineer and frontend developer. Optimize my portfolio so it loads fast, stays smooth, and can handle many users opening it at the same time without slowing down.
</div></blockquote></span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Performance / Speed
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Refactor the app for maximum speed and lightweight rendering.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Remove unused components, heavy dependencies, and unnecessary client-side code.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Use Next.js best practices for performance: route splitting, server components where possible, dynamic imports, and caching.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Optimize all images using next/image, proper sizing, lazy loading, and compressed formats.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Ensure fonts are optimized and not blocking page load.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">Reduce bundle size and avoid unnecessary re-renders.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
